headline: PSE&G's Summer Relief Initiative Protecting Residential Customers from Higher Costs This Summer Moves Forward
summary: Public Service Electric and Gas Company (PSE&G) today announced the New Jersey Board of Public Utilities (BPU) approved PSE&G's proposal to provide all residential customers with a temporary credit that will offer relief on their summer electric bills. The credit will combat the significant electric supply price increase that is the result of PJM's capacity price auction.
